Heat oil in Dutch oven over medium heat until hot. Brown beef in batches; pour off drippings. Return beef to pan; season with salt. Stir in broth and salsa; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover tightly and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Stir in zucchini, beans and corn; continue cooking, covered, 15 to 20 minutes or until beef is fork-tender. Stir in cornstarch mixture; cook and stir 1 minute or until thickened. Serve with toppings.